properties.name: Norte de Santander, Tibú
properties.comment:
Norte de Santander, Tibú.
The polygons presented here represent some of the properties belonging to Bioagroindustrial de Colombia. By comparing the name of the facilities mentioned in Source 12 and cadastral data, it was possible to determine some plots. Finding the other plots was complicated because a lot of properties in the area have the same name, therefore selecting one of them would have some considerable error. The area has extended plantations of palm oil.

properties.name: Las Pavas, Buenos Aires, El Peñón, Bolívar, Colombia
properties.comment:
The shapefile represents two properties that were acquired in 2007 by the Consorcio El Labrador. The polygon on the rights represents the plot known as Hacienda Las Pavas and the one on the left side is "Peñaloza". The first one has 1495 hectares (information from cadastre) and Peñaloza has 198 hectares. It was impossible to determine the location of the landholdings known as "Si Dios Quiere" and "No te canses", because in the department of Bolívar there are several properties with those names and none is similar to the size described on the sources.

Cadastre id numbers:
Hacienda Las Pavas: 132680002000000010110000000000
Peñaloza: 136670000000000030400000000000

properties.name: San Jacinto
properties.comment:
There are two facilities closely related to this case. They are known as "Barcelona" and "Cuba". In the shapefile, the first one was subdivided in several units of around 20 hectares each. The one on the right, Cuba, has an extension of 1010 hectares. These lands were, presumably, illegally acquired by former senator Otto Bula, who is now in Prison. The landholding in between known as "El Encanto" presents vasts extensions of deforestation for commercial forest plantations. It is unsure whether this last one also belongs to this corporation. The extension of the polygons is 1942 hectares approximately. These polygons represent a minimal part of the area in hands of the companies that are linked to the "Corporación Amigos de Los Montes de María"

Cadastre Id Number: Cuba - 136540000000000030136000000000
Barcelona (Just one): 136540000000000020246000000000

properties.name: Riosucio, Chocó, Colombia
properties.comment: This polygon covers the basins of both rivers Curvaradó and Jiguamiandó in the Chocó State of Colombia. It was allocated to those communities on November 22nd of 2000, as stated in the resolution 2809 of the Instituto Colombiano de Reforma Agraria. It is possible that the land allocated is larger, but the land use change is basically happening in this polygon. Source: http://www.consejodeestado.gov.co/documentos/boletines/147/S3/11001-03-26-000-2007-00083-00(34911).pdf (Consejo de Estado). Size of the polygon is 28991 hectares, it cannot be confirmed that all of them belong to the company. It represents some private and collective (from afrocolombian) properties. There are ongoing legal process. In this polygons are the properties mentioned in the Report Nr 54 of the Court of Supreme Justice: Collective land title of afrocolombian Communities of the basins of the rivers Curvaradó and Jiguamiandó, El Tesoro, La Nevera, Las Palmitas, No hay como Dios and Santa Teotista
properties.facility_name: Collective land title of afrocolombian Communities of the basins of the rivers Curvaradó and Jiguamiandó

properties.name: Ovejas, Ovejas, Sucre, Colombia
properties.comment: The polygon shows, according to cadastre data, all the holdings located in the Municipality of Sucre in the State of Sucre with the name "La Europa". It seems that, the once as a unit Finca Europa, has been turned into smaller fragments. This was usually done to obtain more credits from the governments and subsidies for irrigation districts. Although satellite pictures show a clear oil palm plantation, the cadastre georreferenced holdings are not continuous. The land size, according to cadastre data is around 800 hectares. This might have small georrefentiation problems and the lack of some fragments, therefore, the smaller size.

properties.name: Choco, Colombia
properties.comment: The polygons represent all the land under concession held by La Muriel Mining Company under this deal. It must be stated that not all the land is defined for cobber extraction, but some concessions are still under exploration schemes. Additionally, some contracts have already been suspended due to the intersection of the area with indigenous and collective afrocolombian territories.

properties.name: Cajamarca, Tolima, Colombia
properties.comment: AgloGold Ashanti has received several allowance for exploration. In Colomobia, they had almost 8 million hectares for exploration. The polygon in this specific observation refers to the exploration contract Nr. EIG-163, located in Cajamarca and where the mine is supposed to be located. The polygon was extracted from the geographic services of the Agencia Nacional de Minería of Colombia.

properties.name: Codazzi, Agustín Codazzi, Cesar, Colombia
properties.comment:
In Agustin Codazzi, Cesar, the company Oleoflores owns the plot known as Hacienda Las Flores. The uploaded shapefile shows one property where the refineries, mills and extraction plants are located. Around them are several oil palm fields. It is possible that the properties around this plot also belongs to Oleoflores SA, but it is uncertain. The source of the shapefile is the official cadastre of Colombia, developed by the Instituto Geográfico Agustín Codazzi. The coordinates of the biodiesel refinery are from an official document from Corpocesar (Environmental institution).

The exact coordinates of the biodiesel refinery are: -73.2360, 10.0979. Obtained from the official document of Corpocesar for the allowance of air pollution.

properties.name: Santa Marta, Magdalena, Colombia
properties.comment:
The polygons displayed in this deal relate uniquely to the area under control of Palmeras de La Costa, one of the investors participant in Biocombustibles del Caribe. The DAABON group, the other participant in the joint venture, is not displayed in the Land Matrix portal, given that their land purchases were done in the 1970s. Although Palmeras de La Costa has been present in the palm oils business in the state of Cesar since 1970s, several documents report that after the paramilitary violence suffered in El Copey, Cesar, the company attempted to acquired several properties close to their mill. The polygons on the west are already established plantations, which suggest that the company might have been several years there. On the other hand, and according to judiciary documents from the national authorities, the separate plots are involved in a restitution process. According to the national authorities, the company obtained those plots after paramilitary groups had threatened smallholders to abandon and sell their land.

Sources: http://tribunaltierrascartagena.com/sites/default/files/SENTENCIA%202018-00017%20-%20JUANA%20AVENDA%C3%91O%20-%20DRA%20LAURA%20CANTILLO.PDF

- https://www.restituciondetierras.gov.co/documents/10184/514988/200013121003-201500113-00++El+Copey++19+Julio+2016.PDF/535fb02c-e78f-472d-85c2-ffe2f19949ea?version=1.0

Spatial data derived from the Mapathon 2020.

properties.name: Puerto López, Meta, Colombia
properties.comment: According to media reports and official documents (Source 11), the facility name is the Hacienda Cantaclaro, which was acquired in 2003 by the Grupo GPC, which is the parental company of Suministros de Productos Colombianos SA, the operating company of the project. The upload shapefile includes two polygons, which have the presence of cassava fields. Neverhtless, according to cadastre data from the Instituto Geográfico Agustín Codazzi, only the northern polygon is, with certainty, property of the company. The Cadastral number of this land holding is  505730002000000010035000000000.

properties.name: Santa Rosalía, Vichada, Colombia
properties.comment: The areas described in the attached Shapefile were obtained comparing the names of the land holdings mentioned in the Oxfam report "Divide y Comprarás", which was published in 2013. Some characteristics of each holding bought by Cargill and their subsidiaries can be found in the attachment of this report. This information was crossed with Georreferenced data by the Instituto Geográfico Agustín Codazzi and the polygons here displayed correspond to those mentioned in the Oxfam report. There were some difficulties trying to find 4 of them

properties.name: Cumaribo, Vichada, Colombia
properties.comment: The polygons shown in this location are not mentioned in the Oxfam report. It should be stated that there is no certainty on the ownership of these holdings by Cargill or any of its subsidiaries. Nevertheless, by comparing satellite imagery and the location of the Cargill properties, one can suspect that these might have some relationship to Cargill. First, there is a continuity between these plots and plantations present in Cargill areas owned by Cargill. Second, those are large monoculture complexes with irrigation infrastructure that is not found anywhere close to this area. The polygons contained here might have some relationship to Cargill, but it is not certain.

properties.name: Mapiripán, Meta, Colombia
properties.comment:
This deal location is compounded by 7 neighboring plots in the municipality of Mapiripán, Meta. According to the company and georreferenced data for the RSPO certification, they let 3 areas to be certified for this. They are the farms known as "Macondo", "Barandales" and "Las Toninas". Additional to it, the plots known as "Yamú" and "Bogante" are defined by the company as "Strategic Alliances", which mean that independents accept to give their lands for their plantations with renting contracts. Nevertheless, both of the last ones belonged to independent companies represented by the same representative of Poligrow Colombia. According to the company, they also own the farm known as "Majadero" and "Cristalina", the first one being impossible to locate with cadastre data. Finally, in a certification of Naturacert, it is stated that one of their properties is known as Santa Marta. The information was corroborated with georreferenced cadastre data of the Instituto Geográfico Agustín Codazzi and satellite imagery. According to some media reports, the company tried to purchase the holding known as "Hacienda Santa Ana" which has 70000 hectares, but it generated a legal problem in which the company is currently involved.

For more detail on location see:

Source 5
Source 6
Source 7
Source 16
Source 17: https://www.rspo.org/acop/2016/poligrow-colombia-ltda/po-23g_rac_certificado_grupo_v2_%20Poligrow.pdf

properties.name: Puerto Gaitán, Puerto Gaitán, Meta, Colombia
properties.comment:
The coordinates refer specifically to one of the several plots held by Agropecuaria Aliar S.A. They are distributed between Puerto Gaitán and Puerto López, Meta. The polygons shown here were obtained by contrasting media reports, company resources, official documents by the environmental agencies of the government and cadastral data by the Instituto Geográfico Agustín Codazzi. The only remaining plot in this polygon is the one known as "Gramanfey", which was impossible to find. The polygons in this deal are certainly under management of the company, although the managers have found different forms to not be legally attached to them, which might represent a felony.

The company is implementing a sort of sharecropping system with close peasants. Nevertheless, some media reports argue that those peasants are actually members of the company. Agropecuaria Aliar might be holding more land than the one here shown.

See sources 20-24, 26

properties.name: Pivijay, Magdalena, Colombia
properties.comment:
The polygons that represent the area of the firm "Agrifuels" might not be completely accurate. They were obtained from company sources that depict the landholdings. Media sources and documents from environmental authorities let know that at least 2 of the landholdings are known as "El Avión" and "Murillo". It seems that the latest one is now known as "El Puente". This had some legal problems during the land transactions, since the previous owner of the property asserts that the land authority of Colombia (Incoder by this time) allowed the transfer of abandoned land to paramilitary groups. Please see Source 14 for more detail on the location

Source 13, 17, 14

The operations are at an altitude of 3,900 metres above sea level and produce lithium carbonate from the Salar de Olaroz brine resource which contains high concentrations of lithium and potash brine.

properties.name: Asubima Forest Reserve, Ghana
properties.comment:
compartments 1-13, 27 and 28 of the Asubima FR, compartments 8, 19-22, 27, 28 and 33-35 of Afrensu Brohuma Forest Reserve (in 2010) plus compartments 12, 29 and 32 in 2012. Each compartment is 1600m*800m (128ha), thus totaling 1664ha in this reserve.
Asubima FR and Afrensu Brohuma FR share a common boundary over 4,800m of which 1,600m is part of the Form Ghana concessions. 
The Asubima and Afrensu concessions border each other, with the Asubima concession forming the northern part and the Afrenso Brohuma concession the southern part
Spatial data derived from a map on the company website.

properties.name: Western Region, Uganda
properties.comment:
six tea estates which are spread across Western Uganda. 

Shapefile added from satellite Imagery
properties.description: Mwenge Tea Estate is the largest among the six estates owned by MRUL. It is located in the Kyenjojo District of Western Uganda, four kilometres from Mwenge Central, the headquarters of McLeod Russel Uganda Limited. At an altitude of 1440m above sea level, it is 321km from Entebbe International Airport, 274 km from Kampala, the capital of Uganda, and 18 km off the Kampala-Fort Portal road.

properties.comment: Polygon from satellite Imagery
properties.description: Muzizi Tea Estate is located in the Kagadi District of the Bwikara Sub-County at an altitude of 1286 meters above mean sea level. It is 21 km from the District Headquarters in Kagadi Town, 302 km from Kampala and 60 km from our Head Office in Kyarusozi Mwenge.

properties.comment:
Kisaru, was originally, for 22 years, a satellite division of Bugambe Tea Estate and was converted into an independent Estate in 2020. Apart from increasing its cultivated areas for tea and gum, the Estate has set up a new production line. This will result in a production target of 1.59 million kilograms of made tea this year; of which 97% is expected from our own leaf and 3% form bought leaf.
Shapefile added from satellite imagery
properties.description: Kisaru Tea Estate is located in mid-western Uganda, 50km west of Hoima town, in the newly created Kikuube District.

properties.comment: Polygon drawn from satellite Imagery
properties.description: Kiko Tea Estate, in Kabarole District, is the smallest of the Mcleod Russel Uganda estates and covers a total area of 492.02 hectares.

properties.comment: Shapefile added from satellite imagery
properties.description: Bugambe Tea Estate is located in the newly created district of Kikuube in the gentle hills along the Western Rift Valley. The Estate has two divisions: Nyamarobyo and Buseruka comprising tea fields, eucalyptus plantations, natural forests and all the relevant infrastructure spread across 1573.17 hectares.

properties.name: Puerto Gaitán, Meta, Colombia
properties.comment: The map seen in this platform contains all the current area that is conceded to Frontera Energy or its subsidiaries, is already in a production stage and was granted by the government after the year 2000. In total, the company has under concession more than 3 million hectares in Colombia for exploration or extraction. It must be said that this area is not necessarily for extraction, but also for exploration. This amount of land is distributed under different concession contracts, some which were signed at different times. It could also happen that Frontera Energy, previously known as Pacific Rubiales, might have acquired land by the acquisition of some companies and not directly the land. The polygons and all this information was extracted from the Agencia Nacional de Hidrocarburos and its latest update was in February 2019. To extract the original shapefile look at: www.anh.gov.co/Asignacion-de-areas/Documents/Tierras_FEBRERO_220219.zip

properties.name: Meta, Colombia

Those landholdings were acquired by Simplified Stock Companies that were created to circumvent current Colombian legislation.

Source 2

El Chaparral is the name of one of the properties acquired by Monica Seeds, but it is not the name of the facility. 
Source 9 p. 41

La Bonita and Las Mercedes properties are located in the municipality of Cumaribo, department of Vichada.

properties.comment: Lot 3 is found on the western side of the River Ngounié flood plain, the concession overlaps with the catchments of five rivers: Douya, Ivevoula, Doumina, Idigui, and Dibotsa, which have their sources in the Tandou Mountains of the Mayombe Massif to the west and flow eastwards emptying into the River Ngounié. The concession is delimited by the N1 road to the east, the River Douya to the north, the lower edge of the Tandou Escarpment to the west and the River Dibotsa to the south. Location information available in RSPO documentation.
properties.description: Mouila Lot 3 and Lot 3 extension

properties.name: Salar Centenario, Salta, Argentina
properties.comment:
Located 150 kilometers from San Antonio de los Cobres, on the southern edge of the Los Andes department, in the province of Salta. The polygons are the mines included in the project.
It is a huge desert region, located at an altitude of 3,800 m. 50 km from there, the first town is Santa Rosa de Pastos Grandes, it has a population of 300 inhabitants.

The polygon includes all mines of the proyect.

properties.name: Fadeba, Burkina Faso
properties.comment:
The Banfora Gold Project is located in the Province of Léraba, Cascades Region, southwestern Burkina Faso, 90 km southwest of the town of Banfora, the administrative centre of the province of Comoé, and approximately 510 km southwest of Ouagadougou, the capital city of Burkina Faso. The Project is centred at approximately Latitude 10°42’N and Longitude 5°38’W. The approximate centres of the currently delineated mineralized zones are as follows: Nogbele: 230,725mE, 1,114,800mN; Fourkoura: 240,365mE, 1,114,375mN; Samavogo: 257,700mE, 1,115,915mN, and Stinger: 250,030mE, 1,114,350mN (UTM Clarke 1880 ellipsoid, Adindan datum, Zone 30N). Boundary details taken from Technical Report.
Shapefile added from satellite imagery

properties.name: Salar Diablillos, Salta Province, Argentina
properties.comment: Sal de los Angeles project is situated in the prolific “Lithium Triangle” in Salta Province, Argentina and covers almost 100% of the Salar de Diablillos with mining area equal to 8854 ha. The property is located approximately 145 km SW of the city of Salta, a few kilometers north of the provincial border with Catamarca. The entire property is in Salta territory.
